  <data key="d16">strong_textual_inference</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( Article 1 ; Q92,94 ), superstition denotes undue divine worship. Now a thing pertains to the worship of God in two ways: in one way, it is something offered to God ; as a sacrifice, an oblation, or something of the kind: in</data>
