  <data key="d17">As stated above ( II-II:85:3 ad 3 ), the term "oblation" is common to all things offered for the Divine worship, so that if a thing be offered to be destroyed in worship of God , as though it were being made into something holy , it is both an oblation and a sacrifice. W</data>
