  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q080-a001-treated-in-concept-justice-st-ii-ii-q080-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q080.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">al virtue ; and the second is that in some respect they fall short of the perfection of that virtue . Accordingly since justice is of one man to another as stated above ( II-II:58:2 ), all the virtues that are directed to another person may by reason of this common aspect be annexed to</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
