  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q081.a004.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that religion is not a special virtue distinct from the others. Augustine says (De Civ. Dei x, 6): "Any action whereby we are united to God in holy fellowship, is a true sacrifice." But sacrifice belongs to</data>
