  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q081.a005.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that religion is a theological virtue . Augustine says (Enchiridion iii) that " God is worshiped by faith , hope and charity ," which are theological virtues . Now it belongs to religion to pay worship to G</data>
