  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q081.a006.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that religion should not be preferred to the other moral virtues . The perfection of a moral virtue consists in its observing the mean, as stated in Ethic. ii, 6. But religion fails to observe the mean of j</data>
