  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q083-a002-treated-in-concept-prayer-st-ii-ii-q083-a002-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q083.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Among the ancients there was a threefold error concerning prayer . Some held that human affairs are not ruled by Divine providence ; whence it would follow that it is useless to pray and to worship God at all: of these it is</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
