  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q083.a005.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">According to Valerius Maximus [Fact. et Dict. Memor. vii, 2, " Socrates deemed that we should ask the immortal gods for nothing else but that they should grant us good things, because they at any rate know what is good for each one whereas when we pray we freq</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
