  <data key="d17">gilantius consisted in saying that "while we live, we can pray one for another; but that after we are dead, none of our prayers for others can be heard, seeing that not even the martyrs ' prayers are granted when they pray for their blood to be avenged." But this is absolutely false ,</data>
