  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q086.a004</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.86 a.4 — In particular, as to first-fruits, are men bound to offer them?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q086.a004.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that men are not bound to pay first-fruits. After giving the law of the first-born the text continues ( Exodus 13:9 ): "It shall be as a sign in thy hand," so that, apparently, it is a ceremonial precept. B</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
