  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q086.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( II-II:85:3 ad 3 ), the term "oblation" is common to all things offered for the Divine worship, so that if a thing be offered to be destroyed in worship of God , as though it were being made into so</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
