  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">4:21 ): "The offering of him that sacrificeth of a thing wrongfully gotten is stained." Therefore it is evident that an oblation must not be made of things unjustly acquired or possessed. On the Old Law , however, wherein the figure was predominant, certain things were reckoned unclean o</data>
