<edge source="st.ii-ii.q087" target="st.ii-ii.q087.a001" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q087.contains.st.ii-ii.q087.a001">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q087.contains.st.ii-ii.q087.a001</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q087</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.87 — Tithes</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q087.a001</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.87 a.1 — Are men bound by precept to pay tithes?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q087.a001.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that men are not bound by precept to pay tithes . The commandment to pay tithes is contained in the Old Law ( Leviticus 27:30 ), "All tithes of the land, whether of corn or of the fruits of trees, are the L</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q087" target="st.ii-ii.q087.a002" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q087.contains.st.ii-ii.q087.a002">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q087.contains.st.ii-ii.q087.a002</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q087</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.87 — Tithes</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q087.a002</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.87 a.2 — Of what things ought tithes to be paid?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q087.a002.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that men are not bound to give tithes of all things. The paying of tithes seems to be an institution of the Old Law . Now the Old Law contains no precept about personal tithes , viz. those that are payable </data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q087" target="st.ii-ii.q087.a003" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q087.contains.st.ii-ii.q087.a003">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q087.contains.st.ii-ii.q087.a003</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q087</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.87 — Tithes</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q087.a003</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.87 a.3 — To whom ought they to be paid?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q087.a003.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that tithes should not be paid to the clergy. Tithes were paid to the Levites in the Old Testament , because they had no portion in the people's possessions, according to Numbers 18:23-24 . But in the New T</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q087" target="st.ii-ii.q087.a004" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q087.contains.st.ii-ii.q087.a004">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q087.contains.st.ii-ii.q087.a004</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q087</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.87 — Tithes</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q087.a004</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.87 a.4 — Who ought to pay tithes?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q087.a004.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that clerics also are bound to pay tithes . By common law [Cap. Cum homines, de Decimis, etc.] the parish church should receive the tithes on the lands which are in its territory. Now it happens sometimes t</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
