  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q088-a001-treated-in-concept-promise-to-god-st-ii-ii-q088-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q088.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">A vow denotes a binding to do or omit some particular thing. Now one man binds himself to another by means of a promise, which is an act of the reason to which faculty it belongs to direct. For just as a man by commanding or praying , directs, in a fashion, what others are to do</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
