  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.vow</data>
  <data key="d12">Vow</data>
  <data key="d13">act_type</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q088-a004-treated-in-concept-vow-st-ii-ii-q088-a004-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q088.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( 1 and 2 ), a vow is a promise made to God . Now one makes a promise to a man under one aspect, and to God under another. Because we promise something to a man for his own profi</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q088.a005" target="concept.vow" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q088.a005.treated_in.concept.vow">
