  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">ought not, and in like manner as regards other circumstances, as the Philosopher shows (Ethic. iv, 1,2,3). Accordingly superstition is a vice contrary to religion by excess, not that it offers more to the divine worship than true religion, but because it offers divine worship either to whom</data>
