  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As Augustine states (Cont. Mendac. xiv), "a most pernicious lie is that which is uttered in matters pertaining to Christian religion ." Now it is a lie if one signify outwardly that which is contrary to the truth . But just as a thing is signified by word, so</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q093" target="st.ii-ii.q093.a001" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q093.contains.st.ii-ii.q093.a001">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q093.contains.st.ii-ii.q093.a001</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q093</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.93 — Superstition consisting in undue worship of the true God</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q093.a001</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.93 a.1 — Can there be anything pernicious in the worship of the true God?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q093.a001.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that there cannot be anything pernicious in the worship of the true God . It is written ( Joel 2:32 ): "Everyone that shall call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved." Now whoever worships God calls upo</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q093" target="st.ii-ii.q093.a002" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q093.contains.st.ii-ii.q093.a002">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q093.contains.st.ii-ii.q093.a002</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q093</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.93 — Superstition consisting in undue worship of the true God</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q093.a002</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.93 a.2 — Can there be anything superfluous therein?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q093.a002.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that there cannot be excess in the worship of God . It is written ( Sirach 43:32 ): "Glorify the Lord as much as ever you can, for He will yet far exceed." Now the divine worship is directed to the glorific</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
