  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q093.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">A thing is said to be in excess in two ways. First, with regard to absolute quantity , and in this way there cannot be excess in the worship of God , because whatever man does is less than he owes God . Secondly, a thing is in excess with regard to quantity of</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
