  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Men attend to all these observances, not as causes but as signs of future events, good or evil . Nor do they observe them as signs given by God , since these signs are brought forward, not on divine authority, but rather by human vanity with the cooperation of</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
