  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q099.a001.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that sacrilege is not the violation of a sacred thing. It is stated (XVII, qu. iv [Append. Gratian, on can. Si quis suadente]): "They are guilty of sacrilege who disagree about the sovereign's decision, and</data>
