  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q099-a001-treated-in-concept-sacred-thing-st-ii-ii-q099-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q099.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( II-II:81:5 ; I-II:101:4 ), a thing is called "sacred" through being deputed to the divine worship. Now just as a thing acquires an aspect of good through being deputed to a good end, so does a thing assume a divi</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
