  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">hings, has various degrees, according to the differences of sacred things. Among these the highest place belongs to the sacraments whereby man is sanctified: chief of which is the sacrament of the Eucharist , for it contains Christ Himself. Wherefore the sacrilege that is committed against</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
