  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q100.a005</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.100 a.5 — Does real remuneration alone make a man guilty of simony, or also oral remuneration or remuneration by service?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q100.a005.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that it is lawful to grant spiritual things in return for an equivalent of service, or an oral remuneration. Gregory says (Regist. iii, ep. 18): "It is right that those who serve the interests of the Church</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q100" target="st.ii-ii.q100.a006" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q100.contains.st.ii-ii.q100.a006">
